      "writtenOn": "2019-02-22T15:36:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was proposing that we *always* assume that the new task will have 0.75 testedness, not just when stoleFrom was a failure.  I think the math works out in that case.  At any rate, as much as I\u0027d like to have a \"nice\" mathematical solution, I\u0027d be okay with just giving a constant bonus to bisecting failures/mishaps.",
      "parentUuid": "cd00aefd_67c8e97d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1597,
        "startChar": 52,
        "endLine": 1597,
        "endChar": 104
